In article <a_rubin.779994273@dsg4.dse.beckman.com>, 
    a_rubin@dsg4.dse.beckman.com (Arthur Rubin) says:

>A small point.  The RSA patent is not VALID outside of the US; hence it's not
>enforced.

To amplify a bit -- the US Patent Law allows application for a patent
within one year of disclosure (through publication) or offer for sale.

In Japan and Europe, publication will nullify any patent before it
is applied for and, in some instances, before it is issued.
